author: News Tribune
title: Prep Volleyball: Lady Jays down Hickman
text:
Share 
COLUMBIA, Mo. — The Jefferson City Lady Jays defeated the Hickman Kewpies 25-15, 25-22 on Thursday night. 
Mary Wehmeyer had nine kills and five blocks for the winners. Cameryn Campbell had 12 service points and 12 digs, while Baylee Rozier added 11 points and seven digs. Megan Bleidistel added four digs for the Lady Jays (7-14). 
The Lady Jays won the JV match 25-21, 25-11. 
Tori LePage had 12 service points, while Sam Murray had four aces among her nine service points. Stephanie Fisher totaled 15 digs for the Lady Jays (23-8-1). 
In the freshman match, Morgan Surls finished with 20 service points and 10 digs as Jefferson City won 13-25, 25-18, 25-22. 
Maddie Jones totaled nine assists and eight service points, while Maddy Cook had seven service points and seven digs. Zoe Stratman had 13 digs, while Micah Linthacum totaled six kills and five blocks for the Lady Jays (4-16-3). ﻿
